RACE.FOOTNOTES: B D R DRAGSTER tracked pace along the inside, inherited lead when rivals carried out wide, kept to task in deep stretch to hold. B D R BAXTER led along the inside on the backstretch, continued along the inside on the turn, began to lug out midway through the turn and into the lane, ended up in the five path coming into the stretch, lugged back in the lane and came back in a game try. LAMPY bit slow and bumped in at the start, was on heels midway through the backstretch, finally steading approaching the turn, stayed along the rail on the turn and rallied in between rivals in the lane. MONGOLIAN BOX chased leader two wide on the backstretch, continued on the leaders flank on the turn, carried out into the six path late on the turn, and kept on in the lane to lose third late. RUN JONESZ BEGONEZ came in at the start, tracked pace in between rivals, launched bid two wide entering the lane, and flattened out final sixteenth. DIVINELY DIVERSE broke in and bumped rival at the start, stalked pace three wide, floated out into the four or five path on the turn and lacked a bid in the lane. RUN KING STUD RUN tracked pace three wide throughout and failed to respond when asked. OMAHA RUTSCH stalked pace four wide on the backstretch, tried to hold position entering the turn but floated out by DIVINELY DIVERSE into the six path on the turn, after being passed went near the rail and came up empty in the lane. STEWARDS INQUIRY, AFTER REVIEW B D R BAXTER WAS DISQUALIFIED AND PLACED BEHIND MONGOLIAN BOX FOR BOTHERING HIM ON THE TURN
